modules.description: This module serializes OCaml values into XML elements. It supports primitive types like booleans, integers, floats, characters, strings, and units, as well as structured data such as tuples, records, and variants. Use it to generate XML representations of typed data structures programmatically.

This module provides functions for serializing OCaml values into XML, including support for primitive types and structured data like tuples and records. It includes a monadic bind operator for error handling and a function to generate pretty-printed XML strings. Use it to convert typed data structures into readable XML representations programmatically.
